big toe. But recently, Bill Kimble and his

00:07:43.720 --> 00:07:48.180
colleagues found this bone from the middle
part of the foot, it's called a metatarsal

00:07:48.180 --> 00:07:52.600
and it shows us that the australopith
foot, just like what we see with maybe

00:07:52.600 --> 00:07:56.870
Homo habilis or Homo erectus, had nicely
developed arches from front to back and

00:07:56.870 --> 00:08:01.640
side to side, a fully modern human foot
really well adapted for long distance

00:08:01.640 --> 00:08:05.850
