maybe as different as we would have

00:08:05.850 --> 00:08:09.710
thought a long time...or a number of years
ago as a difference between

00:08:09.710 --> 00:08:12.720
australopithecus and human. And if you
blow up an australopith to be about the

00:08:12.720 --> 00:08:17.280
same size you see this really fairly
human-like lower limb, fairly human like

00:08:17.280 --> 00:08:21.070
body shape, and some of the other
differences maybe a little bit less

00:08:21.070 --> 00:08:25.270
dramatic than we thought. So maybe this
transition isn't as dramatic as we thought

00:08:25.270 --> 00:08:31.560
from the australopith side. What can we
